title: Skipping
details: Skipping helps to improve heart rate and blood pressure. It can also help you “boost your immune system, balance your metabolism, and improve your overall health in a short period of time,” according to the British Rope Skipping Association.

title: Pushups
details: Pushups are one of the most basic yet effective bodyweight moves you can perform because of the number of muscles that are recruited to perform them. Strengthen The Whole Body. Improve Your Posture.Burn Calories And Lose Weight. Increase Blood Circulation.Improve Knockout Power And Athleticism.

title: Squats
details: Squats burn calories and might help you lose weight. They also lower your chances of injuring your knees and ankles. As you exercise, the movement strengthens your tendons, bones, and ligaments around the leg muscles.

title: High Knees
details: High knees activate your quadriceps, hamstrings, calves, glutes, and hip flexors, helping improve muscular endurance, balance, and coordination in these muscles. When done at a high intensity and with bounding or explosive knee drives, they can also improve power in your lower body.

title: Mountain Climber
details: As a compound exercise that utilises multiple muscle groups in your whole body, mountain climbers are an effective way of strengthening your arms, back, shoulders, core and legs. Another benefit of using multiple muscles at once is an increased heart rate, which will help you burn more calories.

title: Planks
details: Convenience. Planking is free and takes only a couple of minutes — no gym membership or special equipment required. Protects your back. The ability to brace your core is important for many everyday activities. Prevents exercise-related injuries. Improves posture. Boosts mental health.

title: Flutter Kicks
details: Target multiple muscles. The move activates the hip flexors, the lower back, and the quads a bit more than other exercises, says Kendter. Up cardio health with low-impact. Improve muscular endurance.

title: Crunches
details: The exercise aids in strengthening the core muscles, improving the posture, and increasing the mobility and flexibility of the muscles. When these exercises are performed, the rectus abdominus and the oblique muscles are tightened.

title: Glute bridge
details: It warms up your glute muscles for other exercises. It tones your gluteal muscles. It adds tension to the entire glute bridge motion, increasing the effectiveness of your workout. It strengthens your core muscles, which help you in everyday activities.
